  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "Indexed\nfolder 48 - 202\n997\n\nThe aggregate info exists but it never reaches the machinery which processes it + acts on it, due to the interrupt blank insertion. It doesn't countermand the information with counter information but with no information. It denies information, that actually exists, to the machine. The opposite of a bill of particulars would be a blank page, not a page with any other information of any kind. I am shown how the vicarious atonement works, in an information processing mo",
      "matched_alias": "Bill",
      "term_id": "TERM_bill",
      "term_name": "Bill",
      "term_slug": "bill"
    },
    {
      "text": "Indexed\nfolder 48 - 202\n997\n\nThe aggregate info exists but it never reaches the machinery which processes it + acts on it, due to the interrupt blank insertion. It doesn't countermand the information with counter information but with no information. It denies information, that actually exists, to the machine. The opposite of a bill of particulars would be a blank page, not a page with any other information of any kind. I am shown how the vicarious atonement works, in an information processing mo",
      "matched_alias": "Luther",
      "term_id": "TERM_luther",
      "term_name": "Luther",
      "term_slug": "luther"
    },
    {
      "text": "Indexed\n2\nI try to break away from the time locking collar (clock time) & into the infinite time of any given single form-axis (in space). My motive: I have glimpsed the infinite form axes - as proved in \"UBIK\". &, being forms, are so beautiful that I yearn for them.\n\nI must have glimpsed a form axis prior to \"UBIK.\" Maybe on an acid trip I glimpsed one & intellectually (left hemisphere?) understood it. I knew what it was because once I was a Greek Xtian (1)Platonist; & I knew I had glimpsed inf",
      "matched_alias": "Platonist",
      "term_id": "TERM_platonist",
      "term_name": "Platonist",
      "term_slug": "platonist"
    }
  ],
